text:
you kept on touching me 
to make me feel your presence 
but it wasn‚Äôt just me. 
you kept on saving me from others 
but little did i know 
i should have saved myself from you

you kept on proving me i was the only one
but i guess it wasn‚Äôt just me. 
you kept on harassing me, but i guess it wasn't just me.

you tried to kill me when i raised my voice 
but i guess it wasn't just me. 
because if every woman raises her voice of what she experiences every day, this would've sounded a little different. but sadly, it doesn't. 
women who suffer from sexual harassment are asked to keep their mouth shut. why? because ‚Äú loog kiya kahe gaye‚Äù and most importantly this society!
why have we given so many rights to this society? why can we not just tell everyone to mind their own business and do what we want? or what we want to say. why are we so judgmental?

kyun aurat ka kara hua har kaam stereotype hojata hai ? kyun aurat ko is mashray mein kaam tar samjha jata hai?
is duniya mein aurat woh har kaam kar rahi hai jo ek maard kar raha hai, tou kyun phir bhi aurat ko bura samjha jata hai? awarah samjha jata hai, kyun uski izzat nahi ki jaati? kyun uski izzat pay haat dala jata hai? kyun usko buri nazroon sey deekha jata hai? 
herangi ki baat tou ye hai kay paidah tum saab ek aurat sey hotay ho magar kabhi aurat ki izzat nahi karty. kyun apni mardangi ek aurat ki izzat lay kay deekhani hai ? uski izzat kar kay bhi tou mardangi deekhai ja saktie hai. there are 80% of the women who have been sexually harassed but the society hasn't given them rights to raise their voices. and due to this many have committed suicide, got pregnant. at a young age, got homeless, died because of aids, some got mentally sick.
but there is no stopping. these kind of people  keep on using a woman‚Äôs body to prove their dominance, their superiority. 
we need to unite and fight together for our rights, for our safety and most importantly for "us‚Äù!
stop judging women of what they do and what they wear, and start showing some damn respect and join hands with them to fight for justice.

text:
come join us for the third annual campaign that celebrates women survivors 
the i am bold i rise campaign features thirteen phenomenal women who have risen above their circumstances and are now able to share their triumph with boldness on how they have overcome sexual abuse, depression, bullying, and finding their voice, just to name a few. 
an empowerment calendar, highlighting the women, with work by mad faith photography will be available for purchase featuring each woman.
nathalie mares 
nitzia chama
cristal lopez
reyna maruffo 
maydelli mendoza
anabel herrera
crystal arriola 
melissa mcfarland
rachel brooks
ashourina washington
davina ferriera
sol tomas 
allant√© aniece

it is the mission of this campaign to present the faces of women who may represent your mother, aunt, sister, friend or you when it comes to strength, power, and healing. 
bold ascension was created to inspire hope to women who do not feel worthy of having their voices heard. my mission is to support these women to rise above their circumstances, embrace empowerment and boldly step into their authentic self. i do this through coaching, workshops, awareness campaigns and by connecting women to the resources they need to thrive.

we will have three panelists, ariana sanchez, crystal willis, and judy stella sharing their story on overcoming adversity, a musical performance by tehri green, la mayeya and spoken words by rahbin shyne, davina ferreira, and crystal willis.

‚Å£‚Å£
tony ledbetter, the county gop chair, said the shooting happened sometime between when staffers left the office sunday afternoon and returned monday morning.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
nobody was inside when the shooting took place.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
cheatham says the shooting is being investigated as vandalism until detectives establish a motive.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
ledbetter says it appeared to be by a drive-by-shooter. a window was shot out and another had a bullet hole in it.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
the office is located in a strip mall in south daytona.‚Å£‚Å£

text:
hero or villain?

the women sang, ‚Äúwith a lustrous halo,
she stood there,
high above all;
transforming the melancholic night into day
at such untimely an hour. 
all hail our heroine!
she, who supplanted anguish with hope,
protected us from his criticism.
blocked our tears,
let us choke on our fears no more-
released them to¬†soar high and far!
for she who did this all,

we shall never let her fall!  the men strived to stop us, in vain, forced to take our side.‚Äù the men argued, ‚Äúoh! that femme fatale,

ruthless, iniquitous crook.

ever paused and pondered on how she brought you glory?! charging like a bull,

text:
direct quote: ‚Äúa rush of emotions raced through my body as i realized that i, too, was one of larry nassar‚Äôs victims. the denial poured out of me, and acceptance and anger took its place.‚Äù (p.97)
.
.
.
this moment was one of the absolute most challenging and difficult moments of my life. the fiery hate that burned in me was overpowering. i hated accepting i was victim. it made me feel weak, feel manipulated. accepting that i was abused meant accepting that someone had used me, used my body, and it made me so angry. acceptance is hard. i know. but it is the first step to gaining a strength greater than anything you have felt before.
.
.
.

text: gerry filippatos, a partner at phillips & associates and nina pirrotti spoke about practical considerations when representing clients in harassment cases at the national employment lawyers association fall conference: harnessing the #metoo momentum, which was held in scottsdale, arizona, on october 12-13, 2018. in their talk, they provided a roadmap for representing sexual harassment victims from pre-suit through litigation and trial, including intake, considerations in deciding whether to represent a sexual harassment client, informing the client about the challenges of litigating a sexual harassment case, when the best opportunities for settlement exist, dealing with treating doctors and the client‚Äôs pre-existing conditions, and preparing the client for deposition and trial.

text: jessica barth (right) and caitlin dulany (left) were among the first voices to speak out against harvey weinstein. what followed was a nationwide outcry for accountability against predators and support for victims, helping fuel the #metoo movement. however, just over a year later, while the narrative has begun to shift in favor of victims and monsters like weinstein are sitting behind bars, the need for a safe haven for people in the entertainment industry against sexual abuse has never been stronger. more than one year later, barth and dulany are frustrated that still not much has been done to protect the innocent. that‚Äôs why the two actresses decided to come together and use their voices, along with their industry experience, to form that safe haven: voices in action. by giving victims of all genders the ability to file a digital, timestamped, and private report, the innocent now have the power to decide to keep a protected record of what happened to them that can be handed over to authorities if/when they choose to come forward. secondly, users can opt to be notified if their assailant has been named as a repeat offender, although no personal details will ever be provided. read their stories and about the launch of voices in action in today‚Äôs la times with amy kaufman (link in bio). voices in action is just getting started. stand with us. together, our voices will move mountains. üí™üèºüí™üèΩüí™üèæüí™üèø#voicesinaction from #metoo to #wetoo #harveyweinstein @latimes #latimes #hollywood @iamjessicabarth @caitlindulany

text:
we have developed an industry-wide, accessible means of online reporting of incidents of sexual harassment and abuse, providing referrals to legal and emotional support. victims will be alerted if their alleged assailant has been reported by another victim and given the option to connect through an attorney providing privilege and confidentiality.

we need your support to maintain this much needed platform and we specifically call on those holding power within the entertainment industry to invest in funding this tool for prevention and eventually eradicating sexual harassment and assault and the abuse of power. 
it is imperative that we create a healthy, vibrant roadmap that allows young artists the ability to dream big ‚Äì with joy, curiosity and excitement.

this safer and more equitable community is the community that we are determined to create, and which we unwaveringly serve. 
to those of you who have taken steps in this direction already, thank you. to those who have not yet done so, please join us now. 
follow us on insta @voices_in_action and twitter @voicesin_action to be part of the discussion.

text:
on oct. 18, 2018 the ny times published an opinion piece that offered a perspective that few to none other articles publish - the point of view and regrets of men. on friday afternoon, sept. 21 they posed the question: ‚Äúhad you... ever behaved toward girls or women in ways you now regret?‚Äù they had received 750 responses my monday morning. after making the decision to not publish the stories anonymously, they had to leave out a number of compelling stories because the authors were not willing to attach their names to them for fear of damage to their reputation and job security. ‚Äúmost of the people willing to be on the record were either of retirement age or close to it.‚Äù with the growth of awareness and attention to the issue of sexual assault in era of #metoo, more people have been reflecting on the choices they‚Äôve made in the past and reflecting on them through the lens of a changed perspective today.

these are eight stories of men with regret.

https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/10/18/opinion/men-metoo-high-school.html

text:
playwright, poet and author ntozake shange, whose most acclaimed theater piece is the 1975 tony award-nominated play ‚Äúfor colored girls who have considered suicide/when the rainbow is enuf,‚Äù died saturday, according to her daughter.

she was 70.

shange‚Äôs ‚Äúfor colored girls‚Äù describes the racism, sexism, violence and rape experienced by seven black women. it has been influential to generations of progressive thinkers, from #metoo architect tarana burke to pulitzer prize-winning playwright lynn nottage. after learning of shange‚Äôs death, nottage called her ‚Äúour warrior poet/dramatist.‚Äù savannah shange, a professor of anthropology at the university of california at santa cruz, said saturday that her mother died in her sleep at an assisted living facility in bowie, maryland. she had suffered a series of strokes in 2004.

text:
cuando me preguntan si soy feminista creo que hay un tono capcioso detr√°s.
no interesan las etiquetas, s√≥lo me importa no vivir desde una perspectiva patriarcal.
no quiero vivir desde all√≠ porque no podr√≠a expresar lo hermosa e inabarcable que es la mujer, ni podr√≠a contar que podemos ver un entramado de historias en una sola cosa y que nos cuesta separar el amor de todo lo dem√°s y que eso nos hace bellas. no podr√≠a decidir no querer ser una f√°brica de beb√©s ni conquistar mis derechos reproductivos. no podr√≠a preferir cualquier otro color que el rosa y ser√≠a m√°s atractiva si no hablo.
hoy nos urge hablar.
hoy queremos que el poder se distribuya por igual y queremos tomar las decisiones sobre todo lo que tenga que ver con nuestros cuerpos. hoy no queremos complacer por complacer ni las relaciones de abuso. hoy no nos quepa que nos muestren nada por la calle ni nos sentimos realizadas con palabras al pasar.
somos mujeres y eso es parte esencial e innegable de nuestra identidad; y si queremos somos madres, amantes, esposas; y si queremos cargamos con fantasmas ajenos.
hoy si quiero soy juana de arco, simone de beauvoir o laura ingalls.
hoy si prefiero hago malabarismos.
hoy si quiero soy flor del jard√≠n o fuego derrumbador.
hoy me inclino hacia la uni√≥n.

no hay problemas con nuestra naturaleza, somos maravillosamente perfectas de f√°brica y venimos a regalar esos dones que solo nosotras poseemos; y todo ese poder que hay dentro nuestro no est√° muerto, solo reposaba junto con el dolor y la podredumbre de lo que queda estacionado durante mucho tiempo, y ahora llama para poder salir, pero queremos que entiendan que √©l no quiere hacer la guerra, quiere hacer el amor.

text:
‚Äòawakening‚Äô by @elinkberge awakening is an intimate documentation of a loosely compound, leaderless, and separatist spiritual awakening movement taking shape. elin berge has taken part in different kinds of spiritual women‚Äôs circles in sweden, to capture its people and rituals from the inside.

the women that she photographs believe in the return of ‚Äúthe original goddess‚Äù, a divine feminine essence that is calling women from inside their own bodies. this global movement believes that the awakened divine feminine is going to make women rise all over the world to lead humanity into a new paradigm with a sustainable future and a peaceful, balanced world.
photographs and recorded sound shows women giving into their spirituality in rituals, seeking comfort with each other in sisterhood and making efforts to own their bodies and sexualities. the work opens up to a dialogue about religion and belief in secular sweden and our specific approach to individualism and independence. furthermore, it deals with questions on gender equality and the sisterhood rising all over the world at the moment, most recently the #metoo movement on social media. #almostperfectbymoment

text:
hey folks, for this week's programming we are inviting you to dress up for our halloween party!

however, we want to remind folks that not all costumes are appropriate costumes. all costumes must abide by rainbow resource centre's 'code of conduct.' we have compiled some costumes in the following photos that are not appropriate/unwelcome at this event.

note: if you accidentally dress up in a costume that staff or volunteers deems as inappropriate, we will ask you to change out of your costume into some of the clothes donated to rrc. if you do not wish to change out of your costume, we will ask you to leave programming. we want to make sure rrc is a safer space for everybody so no culturally appropriative, racist, sexist, classist, fatphobic ageist, xenophobic, ableist, etc. costumes will be tolerated or allowed into our space.

if you are unsure if your costume is appropriate, please message us, and we will let you know. hot tip: if you are feeling weary about your costume, its probably a good idea to find a new one!

let‚Äôs have a wonderful time, folks!

look in comments for image descriptions and more info.

text:
‚Äúdouble‚Äù ink on paper
inktober day 29!¬†
i‚Äôve been thinking about doing this one since before inktober started, and i am glad it fits into this prompt.¬† it‚Äôs difficult these days to navigate being a human, period. üòï i had watched the pbs program ‚Äú #metoo , now what‚Äù a while back and under discussion was a certain photo (like so many others online) of a woman with her barely-covered butt featured prominently.¬† one of the interviewees had commented that this was ‚Äúobviously different‚Äù that ‚Äúshe is looking at the camera‚Äù which to the interviewee meant that she was claiming her power as a female.¬†
i spent a lot of time on this social media koan, in which one side of me believes that yes ‚Äì if you want to post a picture like that, go for it, and more power to you, and the other side worries about what kind of culture we are creating, and what kind of behavior these photos encourage.¬† i haven‚Äôt been able to think myself out of that one.¬† the closest i have gotten is the idea that ‚Äúthe author is dead‚Äù. it doesn‚Äôt matter what your intent was when you post those pictures.¬† the audience predisposed to look at that as illustrating female (or male, let‚Äôs not assume that only half the population engages in any specific behavior) power or body pride will see it that way.¬† no one else will.¬† no one searches ‚Äú #booty ‚Äú for pictures of empowerment.¬† i wish i had a better answer.

text:
the rapha house sewing trainers show up for our girls on a daily basis. while the healing process will take a lifetime, those first few months at the safe house are often the most difficult. these girls have experienced horrific trauma and are afraid to trust anyone. our trainers are not just teaching them about sewing, but they are also loving them unconditionally and asking nothing in return.
üíó 
this work would not be possible without the hundreds of individuals behind the scenes: trainers, counselors, house mothers, cleaners, cooks, admin, security guards, and drivers to name a few. would you consider leaving an encouraging comment for our international staff? we'll be sure to pass along the love and gratitude.

.
.
thanks you @myrnaibrahim for organizing the talk. so happy to be a small part of your work.
.
.

text:
google workers fume over executives' payouts after sexual harassment claims
the company had paid millions of dollars in exit packages to male executives accused of misconduct and stayed silent about their transgressions. in the case of andy rubin, the creator of android mobile software, the company gave him a $90 million exit package even after #google had concluded that a sexual misconduct claim against him was credible. while #tech workers, executives and others slammed google for the revelations, nowhere was condemnation of the internet giant's actions more pointed than among its own employees. "multiple company actions strongly indicate that protection of powerful abusers is literally and figuratively more valuable to the company than the well-being of their victims," read the question, which was displayed at the meeting, according to people who attended. "what concrete and meaningful actions will be taken to turn this around?"
.

text:
there is a time and place for everything according to the word.this woman right here is the best boss i ever had. i was so disappointed in the boss i had after sonja, i decided i couldn't work for idiots anymore. lol. sonja was, and still is one of my favorite people in the whole world, i'm so glad we met. let me tell you about that.‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
when i first moved to the desert, jobless, i swear to you this small college i'd never heard of stood out to me. hmm. i went home and looked it up. i saw they had an opening for a career advisor and after reading the job description, i thought to myself that is me to a t! how often does a job description fit you 100%?‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
two weeks later i drove by that college again and felt drawn to it the same way i had been the first time. i told myself if that advisor opening was still available, i would apply. guess what? i got home and looked it up and there it was staring me in the face again. this time i pushed fear aside, applied and completed the ridiculous online assessment with math i had never seen before and haven't seen since, but somehow, by the grace of yah, i passed (so i'm told) that test, was called in for an interview and got the job. woot woot! ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
in less than a year we were downsized, but that doesn't matter. i had met and worked with sonja who introduced me to lupe and that's when my life changed, things started to take shape and now business is taking off! ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
the moral of this story is to trust that little feeling when it comes. you never know who you're meant to meet & the purpose. ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

text:
right now, unfortunately, there are millions of young people being #victimized by #sexualpredators
#childrapists #childmolesters #childabusers #pedophiles. those #children are living in their private hell. most will not tell anyone, until years later. some will never tell anyone - period. 
as children we were victimized, multiple times by multiple people, my siblings and i, didn't say anything for decades. i'm not wanting to be a martyr but everyday, recently i have been thinking about how lonely and isolated i felt because i didn't have the right tools, to deal with being a victim. no one ever said, if someone does so and so to you, you should do so and so. do not get me wrong, my maternal grand mother, referenced incest, a whole lot but her colloquial way of accusing my step-grandfather, of "living with his daughter" didn't resonate with me. i knew it was bad but it wasn't until i was a young adult, did i know, exactly what she meant. 
my maternal #grandmother would have attempted to kill anyone, whom she knew #raped us but her manner, didn't create an atmosphere, where any of us, felt comfortable telling her. it may seem contradictory but for us, it is the reality. she lacked something, that prevented all of us, from confiding in her. 
#parents and caregivers need to create an environment, where children feel not only safe but comfortable, cared for, wanted and believed. 
i felt like burden. it didn't make me, want to confide in her. 
#metootrinidad #metootobago #metootrinidadandtobago #metoocaribbean #metoowestindies #metoo

text:
i spoke briefly at the love your lady parts circle last night about the orgasmic black hole and i realized that perhaps it deserves its own mentioning. üëΩüëÄ
.
next time you're about to orgasm, focus really hard on what it is you feel inside of your body. if you're lucky, you won't lose your arousal. many people find that when they do this they experience a sudden feeling of being very far away from the bottom half of their bodies, almost as though on the other side of the room from what's happening, or experiencing it from afar. this is the orgasmic black hole, and it's a sign that you're not fully connected to your pelvic floor or genitals. üß†
.
it shouldn't be normal to be disconnected from your body, especially during a full body event like an orgasm. however, it's unfortunately very common. you don't necessarily have to have profound sexual trauma to experience something like this. in fact, i prefer to regard its commonality as evidence that it's time to reassess how we view sex and genitals as a society. when we think of our pelvic area as being separate from our bodies- (dirty or somehow wrong)- our experience of it becomes disconnected or even painful. we all know or can imagine what pain feels like, but "disconnect" can come in many forms from numbness to inability to orgasm without fantasy (being stuck in the mind in order to escape the body). ‚≠ïÔ∏è
.
have you witnessed this in your body? try allowing yourself permission to not chase an orgasm and see how it changes your experience. üëæ
.

there is so much strength in walking away.
-
i remember the day i walked away from an unhealthy situation, i felt like a failure. i wondered how people we knew would receive it because they thought we were this picture perfect couple. i wondered how would i heal from such heartbreak. i felt stupid for making that decision.
- 
over time, i realized i made the best decision for me to find me again. this would allow me to be a better parent, a better friend and allow light to shine in my heart again.
- 
don‚Äôt feel weak for walking away, feel empowered because you have done something brave.
-

#newyearnewme 
#journey 
#wespeaktheyspeak

text: the silver lining in this may be that i've found someone who allows me to have control of my body. when i say no, he listens. we could be in the middle of something and if i say i can't, he listens. i've never really had that before. the right to my own body. i've never been able to make that decision. i remind myself that being married doesn't fix what happened to me. it doesn't take the fact that i was attacked away. but it does give me an ally. he reminds me verbally that this is my body. he holds me through the panic and anxiety attacks and gives me a safe place to retreat to. i have been hurt deeply. but my sugar keeps me safe and helps me heal. i don't know what i'd do without this man. this man who changed everything. this man who gave me my voice back. i honestly didn't know that a man could be so gentle and kind. so compassionate and courteous. i am still broken. but i'm getting better. even if it's just one day at a time. #husband#bestfriend#sexualassaultsurvivor#sexuassaultawareness#metoo#reasonstorecover #soberliving #soberlife #addiction #addictionrecovery  #bpd #bpdrecovery #bipolarrecovery #bipolarawareness #anxietyrecovery #gad #anxietyawareness #generalizedanxietydisorder #anorexiarecovery #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #ptsd #ptsdawareness #ptsdrecovery #posttraumaticstressdisorder #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #endthestigma #suicideattemptsurvivor

text_retweet:
this is the time that we must decide to become human beings that are actually living and vibrating higher in this world as opposed to just existing in the midst of it. there will be mistakes along the way but i applaud my brother @kingkhepri from the @thelivesofmen for addressing this issue in the best way we know now and with good intentions leading the way.

#repost
#patriarchy is a system of oppression based on the notion that #men are superior to #women; particularly in education, social and economic status. as #feminist movements developed and sought to dismantle patriarchal structures, extreme forms of feminism emerged and became proxy‚Äôs for anti-maleness. in some cases, these movements became less about gaining equality for women and more about usurping power from men.

there has been a lot of public debate about how toxic men have been (#metoo and #timesup) and rightfully so, but we are missing a great opportunity to educate men and women about the effects of patriarchy, how we both uphold and support the system, and how it harms us - equally.

so here is what i think we should do to graduate this much needed conversation:
1. men - we have to get real honest with ourselves about how we keep messing up. take ownership and be willing to address really hard things about the way you‚Äôve shown up in the world. i‚Äôm talking to myself as i‚Äôm talking to you.

2. women - understand that #feminism, in it‚Äôs truest form is not the emasculation of men, it is the understanding that healing will not occur in isolation and by condemnation. it‚Äôll only occur by having serious dialogue - assuming number 1 above occurs.

3. women and men have to do a better job of listening and holding space for one another. this is difficult shit to unpack. until that happens, the result will be a bigger wedge between us and more finger pointing.

humbly,

jason

text: i try to remind our peer educators on their impact on sexual and reproductive rights all the time but it gets lost in the mundane. even the adults get lost in the daily drudge. young people often feel powerless even at the current political climate considering the power of the vote is reserved to those 18 and older. let me tell you, plenty of young people have had enormous social impact without being legally considered "adults". locally, middle schoolers in alameda county won a district wide battle against sexist dress code. yes, humans. middle school students. 12 year olds are slaying the patriarchy in california and winning. back in the day, students marched and protested against the vietnam war. one year ago students everywhere protested against the national anthem and gun violence. we have solidarity, we have been exercising our amendment rights and showing the world we are unified and we are powerful. do not underestimate your power, young people. never underestimate your worth.

text:
since 2016, nothing will be the same again. what i knew of as a child is forever changed....distorted...lost. 
perception is not reality?
#weltschmerz

what happened to cartoons of my childhood? what happened to the america of my childhood? 
just the beginning of a lengthy series.... they used to be sharp, clean lines and brightly colored.... now they are rough, dirty, twisted and in black and white. 
i hope you like it. it is also a bit of therapy for me realizing a dealing with the state of our country right now.

text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you‚Äôre waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn‚Äôt forthcoming. what most of them haven‚Äôt lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it. 
#nomore #adamcroasdell #eccarius #ignisscientia #lordbothwell #actor #voiceactor #ffxv #preacher #reign #vampire #supernatural #losangeles #women #supportwomen #timesup

it‚Äôs almost november, & that means lovely fall gourds + pumpkins, and time to #vote in the #midterms !!! üòÉ as angry as i‚Äôve been since pumpkin-head took over, i get even more angry at those who are apathetic about voting..
.
.i remember distinctly before the last election, chatting with a shoulder-shrugging millennial at a party who said she wasn‚Äôt voting or would just vote for bernie, & pontificated, ‚Äúhow bad can it get?‚Äù thanks so much for for your indifference & white privileged ‚Äòdoesn‚Äôt affect me‚Äô mentality, you just cast a vote for trump. üò§ a whopping 47% of eligible voters didn‚Äôt vote. that is *infuriating*. i think these past 2 years have more than illustrated it‚Äôs worse than anyone could have imagined & your vote is important!.
.

.

text:
day 29:  so i wanted to share my two cents about the recent sexual harassment allegations in the news. i'd like to believe all the people standing up and speaking out, notwithstanding the theories about the accusers seeking attention and all that. it may be really for the 15 minutes of fame in some cases, but this public disbelief is the reason most of these incidents stay as shameful secrets tormenting the victim, right? 
#inktober2018  #rewritingeve #metoo
so here's a small poem calling out the real perpetrators, charismatic celebrities who are actually pathetic people under their shiny armours:  act iii of your life:

you grew, then
you had your fun
now, you run.

this is the part that follows your smugness,
your negligence of the hurt.
you shattered so many illusions,
many heartbreaks and shaken faiths. 
now is the part where,
you think about your past actions
start second-guessing
the things you took for granted
and caused someone to suffer in your wake 
here is the part where,
you see everything the way you were supposed to
and an anguish of a few generations comes flooding
and you with your diagnosed insomnia
may wither away into the night
a result of your own doing 
this part is payback,
i‚Äôm sorry you‚Äôre bleeding, black and blue
before i‚Äôve even landed my first punch
with my crimson red gloves
only to serve me as props
you see, because it already has
your fear written all over it. 
this phase of your fame,
is one of shame.
the hunt is out for you
you think
¬†it is a wrong time to be rich or famous?
nu-uh, 
it is you that is wrong for this point in time. 
so you run
or you man up
and own up.
apologise.
because that is all i‚Äôve ever wanted.
also, ¬†i‚Äôm not you. i‚Äôm me

text:
#thisisapainting ‚Äúyou are not alone‚Äù
i forgot this note was in my pocket, more than once and for long periods of time.  almost the same way i've forgotten this truth again and again for myself. .
you are not alone in feeling lonely.
you are not alone in your depression.
you are not alone in your anxiety. 
you are not alone in your abusive relationship.
you are not alone after being raped, sexually abused, and/or sexually assaulted.
you are not alone in your suicidal thoughts. 
you are not alone in your eating disorder. 
you are not alone in trying to parent (well). you are not alone in your secret pregnancy. 
you are not alone in your marriage. 
you are not alone in your bipolar tendencies.
you are not alone in your pain. 
you are not alone in...
you are not alone in this world. 
not today and not ever. .
i can not even begin to tell you how important this sentence is.  and how important you and your well being are.  you are not alone.  not ever.  this is just a painting.  but it's a painting with an idea that could dramatically change your life if you let it.  i have so much more to share, but today please know there is an open hand extended for you to receive if you need help. .
you are not alone.  life is not meant to be lived alone.  so let us live it together. üíõü§ùüíõ
.

text:
what is my lullaby,
is your story too!
the silence in me was the void in you.
now that you pinch it, this wound, so blue.
i realise that the pain, the trauma was true.
all these years i silenced my voice,
hush! hush! little girl,
don't you make a noise.
all these years, terrified under your spell.
now i wake up, now i will yell.
because its time to start anew,
"it was not me, it was you, it was you!"
i am niether afraid, nor ashamed to say.
yes, me too.
yes, me too.
.

text:
in truth who needs yet another entry in one of the longest running horror franchises ever, 11 films in & you‚Äôd have thought every possible eventuality had been covered, we‚Äôve had multiple direct sequels, one unrelated story & a remakes which also spawned a sequel, thankfully we have yet to see #michaelmyers head to space (he looks to be leaving that to jason‚Ä¶thankfully) though it is safe to say the well has really been run quite dry. more problematically a once scary antagonist & one of the most iconic horror ‚Äúmonsters‚Äù ever to walk the silver-screen has been given so much backstory that he has been rendered entirely open-book with familial-ties to his vicitms & many a motive in place of the terrifying ‚Äúshape‚Äù that was simply a force of pure-evil who ‚Äúgraced‚Äù #johncarpenters original, michael myers had long since become just another over-explained serial killer with a mask.
the news that producer #jasonblum (he behind the likes of #getout , #thepurge #insidious & #happydeathday) & writers/director #dannymcbride & #davidgordongreen (they behind, inexplicably, #pineappleexpress & #yourhighness ) were to bring us yet another sequel did not sound overly promising, particularly given mcbride‚Äôs inconsistent quality in comedy, let alone turning his hand to horror. however allow those fears to be allayed, beginning with the choice to bring back #lauriestrode (#jamieleecurtis) for an integral role & throwing out all films bar the original green & mcbride effectively reset the board so to speak, giving them carte-blanche to jump off from the iconic original with a new far better sequel concept that takes place 40 years on from that fateful night.
simplicity is the key here, not that this is a simple film, it just feels that way, short, sharp & too the point as all great slasher films are, streamlining plot & slicing away anything superfluous honing in on the good vs. evil, hunter vs. hunted concept that served carpenter‚Äôs film so well.  the simplicity begins with the choice to call this simply #halloween , it was a risky proposition inviting callbacks to its namesake given what you‚Äôre living up to but much like #jurassicworld & #starwarstheforceawakens #halloween2018 is

text:

text:
the #metoo movement began in 2006, when civil rights activist tarana burke had a conversation with 13-year-old heaven. heaven confided in tarana, who was in shock and unable to respond ‚Äì the only thought running through her mind was ‚Äòme too‚Äô. on october 15, 2017, alyssa milano, an american actress, tweeted asking people to respond to her tweet if they had ever been subjected to sexual abuse. this tweet reignited the campaign that burke commenced over a decade ago. the movement brought focus to the obstacles that women face in their professional and personal lives, while encouraging conversation about women‚Äôs issues and how to tackle them. on december 6, time magazine named ‚Äòthe silence breakers‚Äô as the 2017 person of the year, in honour of all women involved. burke‚Äôs aim for the movement is to create a ‚Äòframework to end sexual violence‚Äô, ‚Äòadd more resources for survivors by providing leadership training and guidance for the community', and to provide a ‚Äòspace for community healing‚Äô. following metoo, there was an increase in the web traffic and access to the online helpline services. social activism groups were also formed to promote a healthy environment both at home and in a work environment. with all the accusations that came out, the gravity of the problem became clearer. reforms have been taken by the american government to increase the processing speed of sexual harassment complaints, and to file it within 180 days. time's up, a movement founded on january 1, 2018, only helped fuel the support that poured in for this movement. roberta kaplan, a lawyer, co-founded the time's up legal defense fund with an aim to provide legal aid to victims of sexual violence, especially in the workplace. tina tchen, head of the chicago office of white-shoe law firm buckley sandler llp, is also helping build this fund. now, a year later, #metoo is a global movement that transcends colour, religion, ethnicity, and gender. it grew to stand as a hashtag for people of all genders who had been sexually assaulted, while following their motto ‚Äì empowerment through empathy.
(continued in comments...)
.

text:
since 2016, nothing will be the same again. what i knew of as a child is forever changed....distorted...lost. 
perception is not reality?
#weltschmerz

what happened to cartoons of my childhood? what happened to the america of my childhood? 
just the beginning of a lengthy series.... they used to be sharp, clean lines and brightly colored.... now they are rough, dirty, twisted and in black and white. 
i hope you like it. it is also a bit of therapy for me realizing a dealing with the state of our country right now.

tomorrow, oct. 30, 8:30am-6pm @smfaattufts #repost @louder_than_words_art_activism with @get_repost
„Éª„Éª„Éª
the billboards highlight: 
the challenges faced by those who fear reporting due to retaliation, fraught relationships with law enforcement, stigma, or fear of detention and deportation. 
the link between domestic violence and gun violence, shining a spotlight on women who are often forgotten ‚Äì those shot and killed by intimate partner violence. in fact, it isn‚Äôt strangers, friends or acquaintances who pose the biggest threat to women ‚Äì it‚Äôs those they date, marry or partner with.

the past and present mistakes of white-centered feminism by insisting that fortifying the movement means centering the voices of those consistently dismissed or left out of the conversation -- women of color. 
women on the move extends beyond the confines of traditional classrooms and museums to interrupt the visual landscape, traversing the city before stopping at schools, parks and other public spaces where people congregate. in each location, volunteers will engage people in conversation about the issues while offering free artist-designed posters that focus on victim blaming and why people are reluctant are report. participants will have access to a resource center with videos, oral histories, informational brochures and artworks that address the definition of consensual sex, how to prevent blaming the victim, strategies to engage men, and dismantling rape culture. 
for freedoms town hall: #metoo and substantive structural change: october 30, 12:10-1:50pm, smfa at tufts, 230 the fenway, boston, 02115, performance room (b209)

this will be a¬†¬†robust conversation addressing common misconceptions and harsh realities including: 
how can victims and survivors gain access to justice and support for the wrongdoing they have endured? 
how can we support those working in low-wage industries where the lack of financial stability makes them vulnerable to violence and exploitation? 
what are the particular challenges faced by women whose experiences are the most marginalized? 
how can we create greater equity in our legislatures, boardrooms, executive offices, and classrooms?

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i‚Äôve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i‚Äôm about to go back, knowing what i know, and we‚Äôre about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump‚Äôs election, trumpeted the return of their ‚Äúpopulist hero‚Äù on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication‚Äôs announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there‚Äôs any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i‚Äôm leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents ‚Äì on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i‚Äôve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i‚Äôm about to go back, knowing what i know, and we‚Äôre about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump‚Äôs election, trumpeted the return of their ‚Äúpopulist hero‚Äù on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication‚Äôs announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there‚Äôs any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i‚Äôm leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents ‚Äì on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

secrets, power and sexual attachments are scorpio‚Äôs domain. jupiter is a force that brings more & bigger wherever it is. almost 1 year ago jupiter entered scorpio, and immediately #metoo happened, bringing so many secrets out, and forcing massive, public confrontations with power dynamics and sexuality. mercury (the mental force) comes together with jupiter today, and both form a trine with chiron. chiron represents psychological healing and awareness that is built through personal journeys in struggle and suffering. pisces is a symbol for the collective unconscious, or the waves of cultural sentiment/sediment we‚Äôre all constantly swimming in. .
today‚Äôs affirmation is a nod and deep bow to all who‚Äôve risked coming forward and sharing stories. sexual abuse and power dynamics are nothing new, but collective courage that builds momentum to talk about them like we are, is. the more stories are shared, the more we each can carry them together, and the less anyone needs to suffer alone. the less isolated we are, the more we will build healing, respect and compassion into our shared futures. .
as we enter mercury‚Äôs shadow, reflect on what stories you need to share. if you‚Äôve been a perpetrator, even if you were ignorant of your own impact at the time, admit and atone for the pain you‚Äôve caused‚Äìdon‚Äôt hide what you know is true‚Ä¶ your healing is tied to suffering you‚Äôve (re)created. if you have a story of pain, you now live in a world that can hold that story with you. reach out for support. our pain can bring us together, and our healing will show us the way through.
.
thank you #taranaburke
name: Embodied Astrology

text:
can not||
you can't handle 
feminine mouths
that speak,
fearless and honest
and refuse to kiss. 
you can't see tongues
not tied anymore 
to ideas and thoughts
that you approve of,
or the tongues
 we bit all these years
 by our own teeth 
only to be silent. 
you can't stand 
the lips
that don't move 
the way you want them to 
that measure no skin
but part away speaking 
for their own flesh and bones
and the way you crawled on them 
inch by inch
tear by tear
breath by breath
without fear and terror. 
you can't take
jaws that now relax
and move up and down 
cussing you straightaway
as you eye them

tongues and teeth

text:
look for the article in the bio.

with the #metooindia movement catching up in india, the levels of ignorance i was witnessing on the topic of sexual harassment was really getting to me. how could something so commonplace, something so everyday be so invisible to so many people? i started this project off as a rant, and then, invited people (mostly women and other survivors) to share the little things they everyday to, as an altered behavior, to protect themselves from sexual harassment. all their stories and lists along with weeks‚Äô worth of secondary research is this essay. i encourage every single one of you to read and share this. it talks to the how women use cities, how they fear when they‚Äôre out on the streets, and how this affects/reinforces how cities are built. link in bio.

text:
it was a real one's birthday yesterday. üéÇ #scorpioseason
realness continues with an essay that is particularly relevant. (this is also to show you that my side eye has never changed.)üí•ü¶Çüêç
.
.
"at first, it used to bug me when he‚Äôd ask me all of those things, and i don‚Äôt remember when it happened, but one day i finally turned around and said, ‚Äúyou know you raised me to handle myself,‚Äù and without missing a beat, my dad said something that i‚Äôve come to hear far too often in different contexts, but particularly in this #metoo flashpoint - ‚Äúi know. but i didn‚Äôt raise everyone else.‚Äù
.
.
in these instances, and probably a whole bevy of other ones but i didn‚Äôt acknowledge the weight of them, my father‚Äôs love language was the norm for me. just like when i would say ‚Äúi love you‚Äù and he would say ‚Äúi know,‚Äù and i would have to poke him to verbally say that he loved me too, knowing that his actions and other combination of words communicated the same four words in different ways. üåπ
.
.
this indirectly taught me how to communicate my love or affection for those in my life in ways that weren‚Äôt always enough, just like how i would poke my dad to say it, i would in turn be poked. however, in light of the conversations around consent, healthy boundaries, and sexual assault and trauma, i‚Äôm realizing that i could have done a better job at ensuring that i sought out consent from all of my relations on how they wanted me to show up for them. it would have saved all involved from some unnecessary disappointment if i had stopped assuming that folks knew the type of friend i was, or how i would or could show up." üôèüèæ
.
.

text:
join us november 8th for the opening our of new exhibit- our bodies remember! this exhibition features six artists grappling with the adversity of existing in their bodies, when others have inflicted emotional, physical, and psychological pain, taking illicit ownership of their autonomy. come witness rachel l‚Äôs ‚Äúcomplex trauma: a memoir‚Äù-a multimedia piece that invites the viewer to rearrange the rocks which are painted with the fragments of rachel‚Äôs trauma narrative.
.
‚Äúsix years after 8th grade, i now lay my story out on the table again for you.  and here it is, in images and fragments because i have found that this disjointed, multi-layered, and multi-media format best serves the complexity and multiplicity of repeated childhood trauma. the definition of narrative is ‚Äúa sequence of connected events.‚Äù a narrative‚Äîa story‚Äîfollows logic. but trauma, especially repeated trauma, is not logical.  memory is not sequential. and, more importantly, when i‚Äôm experiencing a flashback into my trauma, i‚Äôm not thinking about words, connections, or explanations‚Äîi‚Äôm seeing an image stripped of reason. i‚Äôm seeing senseless, illogical violence.
.
the reason i have chosen rocks for this project is because rocks, in many ways, are representative of my memories of trauma. they are ‚Äúpre-narrative‚Äù (some of the most ancient forms of storytelling were told in glyphs on cave walls). they are non-sequential (they can be arranged in a variety of different formats). they are heavy. they are layered. they can stand on their own or they can come together as a collection‚Äù
.
.
.
.
.
.

amazing new music from @avrillavigne. this song made me cry when i first heard it yesterday ... when i was drinking i felt like i was drowning and falling and my voice is what saved me. i fought against the mainstream messages that everyone binge drinks and i was fine. i knew i was drowning. never give up when you feel lost...we can find the help we need to heal üíì

i've gotta keep the calm before the storm
i don‚Äôt want less, i don't want more
must bar the windows and the doors
to keep me safe, to keep me warm
yeah, my life is what i'm fighting for
can‚Äôt part the sea, can't reach the shore
and my voice becomes the driving force
i won't let this pull me overboard

god, keep my head above water
don't let me drown, it gets harder
i'll meet you there at the altar
as i fall down to my knees
don't let me drown, drown, drown
don't let me, don't let me, don‚Äôt let me drown

text:
hey everyone i have decided to do a series of posts so you can understand why it is that i am so passionate about the work i do. it's a bit of my life story so far and it's very personal, so has taken me a lot of courage to share, but if i can reach out and relate to anyone out there that i can help, it'll be so worth it ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è from anorexic high school dropout to teaching a bunch of hormonal women about nutrition!

where did it all begin?? i often get told i‚Äôm really calm, in great shape, look great for my age and are super healthy. each time i hear this it makes me smile because quite honestly years ago this couldn‚Äôt have been further from the truth.

let me take you back to when i was nearly 15 years old, sadly my mum passed away and life was completely turned on its head for me.
i went from being a straight a student to skipping school and rebelling against everything and everyone.
i made poor choices and started hanging about with a ‚Äòbad‚Äô crowd including bagging myself the ultimate ‚Äòbad‚Äô boy, lets call him ‚Äòdick head‚Äô for sake of anonymity!! luckily, i was sensible enough not to get involved in taking drugs, but ‚Äòdick head‚Äô did, and i became the brunt of his bad moods when he was coming down from a high. 
the ultimate punishment was when he wanted sex and i didn‚Äôt ‚Ä¶..well you can join up the dots! at only 16 i didn‚Äôt realise that this was rape because i was in a relationship with him after all, but the scars from it lasted long into adult life!

with the continuous grief from losing my mum and after this traumatic ordeal i felt like i needed to punish myself, felt disgusting and just if i‚Äôm honest wanted to die. i started to binge eat followed by vomming then felt even more disgusting so didn‚Äôt eat for about 5 days after. this pattern of bulimia and anorexia followed for so many years and really messed up my body and health. my periods stopped, i was exhausted, my hair was falling out and my skin looked grey!

i was a physical and emotional wreck!! tune it tomorrow to see how i thought dancing was the solution!

the photo is when i was actually recovering age 27 but still thin hair and bloated face

text:
i started using essential oils 4 years ago. it became an accidental business, as we all naturally speak about the things we love and are passionate about. 
i was blogging, leading worship, running our coffee shop, managing 8-9 employees all while being a mom to 2 little ones. i didn‚Äôt have to do the business, but something inside was nudging me to do it. in fact, i would share the business side of things to friends saying ‚Äúwhat if something happened to my/your  husband?‚Äù what i really meant was an accident or loss of job- and then what? left with a final paycheck and forced to be head of household, financially?! well, little did i know that i would end up being a single mom- and not because of an accident or loss of job. but infidelity, which is way too common these days üíî. my world got ripped out from under me without a conversation and i quickly had to figure life out for my children and i. 
the past 11 months have not been easy, but encouraging as i‚Äôve seen gods hand of provision over my life. he knew the evil and nightmare coming for me. he set me up with a business that has been a lifeline- financially, but even more....a community of women who have loved on me.

i am thankful for young living. i love my oils, but i‚Äôm passionate about this business. i am a silver leader, but my girl @butterflysparks is running hard for diamond üíé this month. our team is full of hard working women and moms who want more for their life and together we provide all the tools to anyone who is interested in building their own side hustle.

i‚Äôm passionate about equipping women with tools to build a business.....especially for the what if. y‚Äôall, i never dreamed my life would look this way. we do not need to live in fear, but it certainly doesn‚Äôt hurt to plan for your future. did you know that your young living business is willable to your children? i‚Äôve never had a job with this option/perk. unbelievable! 
this is my season of hustle- but because of the business i had already built, i was gifted the time to pause and wrap my head around life when it didn‚Äôt pan out the way i had dreamed. it‚Äôs time to run hard....and i‚Äôm looking for women to link arms with and take with me.

text: ‚Äúwomen vs men‚Äù ‚Äúboys vs girls‚Äù- toxic side-effect of the beautiful and powerful ‚Äúmetoo‚Äùmovement; don‚Äôt recall this movement being called ‚Äúmetoo (only females)‚Äù. how shameful to attribute gender to a movement being fought against pure ‚Äúpowerplay‚Äù. more than learning, this is the time to ‚Äúunlearn‚Äù facts that contribute to such twisted ideologies; unlearn what gender and gender roles mean; unlearn what masculinity and femininity means. relearn what it means to be in power and the politics surrounding it; relearn what it is to invade a personal space and what quantifies as abuse- see the issue through a lens devoid of gender. this is not about what we learned but what we did not unlearn! we get conditioned, without our knowledge, even as a child due to the environment around us and it is time to decondition and relearn. this is about ‚Äúsurvivors against abusers‚Äù; ‚Äúprey against predators‚Äù. this powerplay that has affected both women and men. yes, it has affected women way way way more because we live in a freaking patriarchal society! those who think we don‚Äôt, ask the women in your lives before you retort to my post. if none of the women in your lives feel so, kudos to you for creating an equal environment for them but believe me, most women don‚Äôt! and yet, i find people sympathizing with the predator- sympathizing with the poor lion who got to eat the goat and finding fault with the goat for crying out for help! i personally know of boys and men who were violated and i know a lot of them will not come out. because it is not men-like/boy-like to complain; to cry out loud; or to show any kind of emotion- that is what we do to our boys/men- to keep up their so called ‚Äúfaux masculinity‚Äù. and god forbid, they cry, they are not ‚Äúreal‚Äù men- anomalies! so, to people sitting on their gilded chairs spewing lofty ideologies (both women and men)- stop pitting women against men (we already have patriarchy doing that for us) and start seeing the movement for what it actually is- abused vs abusers - fight against bloody powerplay! a voice for all those survivors! #metoo #metooindia #bharatanatyamdance #dance #bharatanatyamdancer

text: i‚Äôm starting the week off by sharing a little piece of my story. when i broke up with my abuser (my family helped me plan an escape-style breakup), i changed my phone number and blocked him from social media. email was the only way he could contact me. and boy, did he take advantage of that. everyday, i would get panic attacks just thinking about checking my inbox. i‚Äôm not sure why i replied to him, but i did for months. one day, he had accused me of cheating on him‚Äîthat‚Äôs the only way he could explain how i was able to move out so secretly. in this same message, he also throws the blame back on me telling me he never gave me a reason to think he‚Äôd hurt me (oh, the the bruises and the abuse wasn‚Äôt a good enough reason then???). i am sharing this not so that you feel bad for me, but so that if someone talks to you this way you understand exactly what‚Äôs happening to you: this is abuse. this is toxic. this is unhealthy. and no one deserves to be spoken to this way or treated this way. if you or even one of your friends is in a relationship like this, feel free to dm me. i want to be there for you, because as you can see, the friends who were there for me saved my life when they helped me move away from that monster. üíúüíô all my her love, stevie #weareher

text:
we often crave for a candlelight dinner, lots of love and a hell lot of attention. that is also, the place where we fall prey. for we think, love is all about attention and perfect dates. ahem!

ladies, it's alright. i agree with you and even understand you. but, know what, for a second, think, would that last life-long? a marriage won't give you your identity.

i had a perfectly planned arranged marriage. it didn't work but. i don't want to elaborate on those details as i don't want to play as a victim. because i am not. 
invest, in your career. in yourself.  save money. make a strong base for yourself from which it is not possible to push you away, or pull you back! 
career, education, money. your career, your education and your money. note the difference. - anon.

text:
sacred union

de afgelopen weken heb ik een heleboel shit opgeruimd in mijn relatie met mannen/het mannelijke met de plantmedicijnen en retreats bij yama, zodat ik vanuit mijn vrouwelijke essentie mannen in vol vertrouwen en liefde kan ontvangen. 
en zonet kreeg ik een aanbod van een mooie man om mijn badkamerlamp op te hangen. een simpele daad, maar dit kan mij juist nu zo raken!!! ‚ù§Ô∏è zo dankbaar dat er mannen zijn in de wereld en dat ik beetje bij beetje hun liefde in duizend vormen weer mag ontvangen. aho! 
om nog meer helderheid en genezing te ervaren in de disbalans tussen mannelijk & vrouwelijk in mijzelf (hieros gamos) en in relatie tot een geliefde (sacred union), ga ik eind november naar de sacred union retreat bij yama. het voelt als zo diep thuiskomen bij haar wijsheid, de diepe verbinding met pachamama, de plantmedicijnen, en het thema heilige huwelijk, wat als een rode draad door mijn leven loopt. hoe kunnen mannen en vrouwen in harmonie samenleven? hoe kunnen we als brothers & sisters verbinden en toch de spanning van de polariteit ervaren? hoe breng ik mannelijk & vrouwelijk in balans in mijzelf? hoe eer ik mijn vader en mijn moeder? hoe kan seksualiteit in vrijheid stromen tussen mij en een geliefde? wat betekent het echt om vrouw te zijn, en hoe ben ik vrouw in relatie tot een man? hoe ben ik een ontvankelijke, vrouwelijke bedding waarin een man helemaal man kan zijn? 
op deze thema‚Äôs heb ik de afgelopen weken vele inzichten, genezing en heling ontvangen in de ayahuasca retreat en de womb wisdom retreat bij yama.  ik ervaar een diepe transformatie en genezing op hele oude trauma‚Äôs die zich nog diep verscholen in de kerkers van mijn ziel. soul retrieval. ik heb heel pijnlijke ervaringen mogen doorleven en mijzelf bevrijd van diepe wortels die mij gevangen hielden in het herhalen van trauma. 
dit heeft meteen effect op mijn relaties tot mannen. ik ben onder ogen gekomen hoe ik zelf steeds opnieuw mijn misbruik-verhaal heb gecre√´erd. hoe ik zelf situaties cre√´er die mijn pijn bevestigen in plaats van genezen. ik heb mannen op mijn knie√´n om vergeving gevraagd. ik leer om mannen opnieuw ten diepste te ontvangen in liefde en vertrouwen. >>>
name: Krista Steenbergen

text:
coach steve kerr calls u.s. ‚Äòbroken 
country‚Äô after synagogue massacre ‚Äúnobody in this country should have a semiautomatic weapon of war,‚Äù the outspoken golden state warriors coach said.

golden state warriors coach steve kerr has been one of the sports world‚Äôs go-to guys for speaking out on the issues.

after a gunman armed with an assault-style rifle and handguns killed 11 people at the tree of life synagogue in pittsburgh, the coach wasn‚Äôt about to go silent.

he told reporters before sunday‚Äôs warriors-nets game in brooklyn that more athletes and coaches are voicing their opinions ‚Äúbecause the times call for it. it‚Äôs easy to feel how broken we are right now as a country and everybody can have influence, not just our political leaders.‚Äù he urged voters to do the talking in the nov. 6 midterm elections ‚Äï as he would on gun control specifically. ‚Äúnobody in this country should have a semiautomatic weapon of war,‚Äù he said, as shown in the clip above. ‚Äúi‚Äôm going to vote for every candidate that‚Äôs willing to stand up to the nra and say you know what, this is insane. we‚Äôre murdering each other every day. we have to get rid of bump stocks. we have to get rid of high-capacity magazines. ... other countries don‚Äôt go through this.‚Äù kerr, whose father was murdered by gunmen in 1984, said earlier in his news conference that shootings in schools, churches, synagogues and movie theaters no longer surprise us. ‚Äúwe need our leaders to step up, unite the country with the appropriate words, the appropriate actions, and we‚Äôre not getting that right now,‚Äù he said, per the new york post.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that‚Äôs what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him ‚Äúwe can take it.‚Äù no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it‚Äôs a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it‚Äôs easy to come along for the ride. there‚Äôs no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they‚Äôre both just characters on the television.

that‚Äôs what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it‚Äôs not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it‚Äôs that we‚Äôve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

that‚Äôs what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him ‚Äúwe can take it.‚Äù no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it‚Äôs a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it‚Äôs easy to come along for the ride. there‚Äôs no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they‚Äôre both just characters on the television.

that‚Äôs what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it‚Äôs not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it‚Äôs that we‚Äôve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
the depth of your devotion is always being tested. 
devotion to what? 
truth.
spirit.
god/goddess. 
source.
the creator.
it is what you do with your energy that matters most, not what you say you‚Äôll do or what you say you believe in.
your presence communicates your intention.
your vibration delivers your message.
there‚Äôs nowhere to hide. 
the veil is gone. 
the curtain no longer exists. 
it‚Äôs all out on the table now.
what are you going to do with it is the only question you need to be asking yourself? 
i am no longer afraid of the gifts that i was sent with. 
for they have become magnified, unified, and quantified by my practice. 
i can see right through anything that is not aligned with integrity within me and around me.
and finally, i no longer feel responsible for vibes that aren‚Äôt mine. 
for a long time, it made me want to hide.
i couldn‚Äôt believe how many people were full of lies, deception, judgment, and straight up malice. 
it hurt my heart, my mind...my everything.
it choked me.
and after a while, it almost broke me. 
once i got over the phase of taking it all personally, it simply drained life-force from every part of my body and soul. 
over time, my guides revealed the highest truth, and the only place to go from there was up and into my own mastery.
if you think this is about mastering anything other than the self, you are dangerous to society. 
during this waning gibbous phase of the moon, let yourself be lifted by the gift of your hard work.
this is a time to appreciate, deeply. 
don‚Äôt forget to celebrate the life that you are living.
ground it in the body.
the vision.
the mission. 
the breath. 
let it move through you this time.

text:
this time of the year will always be hard for me. my body doesn‚Äôt feel damaged as it did before but my mind constantly lives in those moments. 
moments of terror, helplessness and fear. where the most broken pieces of me rush to the surface and i can‚Äôt make sense of what‚Äôs real and what‚Äôs not. 
however in many ways it has made me stronger. i have learned that my courage and bravery know no bounds. 
i know a deeper more profound empathy than i ever thought possible, towards other survivors and towards other‚Äôs suffering. 
but between those moments, don‚Äôt think about what can happen in a month. don‚Äôt think about what can happen in a year. just focus on the 24 hours in front of you and do what you can to get closer to where you want to be #believe

text:
good morning and happy monday! i can‚Äôt believe it‚Äôs the last 3 days of october, but after lackluster month reading wise (since it took me so long to finish one book) i‚Äôm happy to report i finished two this weekend! .
.
.
‚≠êÔ∏èreview: all we ever wanted by emily giffin‚≠êÔ∏è
.
.
.
so, i‚Äôve never read any of giffin‚Äôs other books so i didn‚Äôt know what to expect, but the synopsis of this hooked me from the moment i read it. giffin‚Äôs writing isn‚Äôt *brilliant* but her story line is. wow is this book relevant. it‚Äôs about a snapchat of a young woman that gets sent around, taken after she‚Äôs passed out at a high school party. it takes place in the high powered suburbs of nashville‚Äôs elite. rich parents, spoiled high schoolers, and the ivy league at stake. .
.
.
this book flies by but it does deal with sensitive material (sexual assault, suicide, white male privilege) so i would read with caution if any of those things are tough for you. but in the end, i couldn‚Äôt put this book down and it gave me slight hope that even if the system is refusing to change, maybe just maybe people can learn from their mistakes. have you read it? what did you think? i loved nina so much.

american screen darling gabrielle union clocks 36!

from pulling a gwen stefani at her 90s-themed party in miami, florida on saturday night, to crashing the headlines yet again ( and why not, it's her birthday!!), we can't help but celebrate this talented beauty.

ever since the world said hello to this black american sweetheart many thanks to featuring in "small movies" like: love & basketball, she's all that and 10 things i hate about you, which became instant hits, we knew the former model will forever embrace the spotlight.

the star's big break came in 2003, when she featured in the film; deliver us from eva. she's since gone on to star in big project movies including; daddy's little girls, the perfect holiday, cadillac records, think like a man, think like a man too and others, establishing herself firmly as one of hollywood's most sort after actresses.

in 2017, union decided to launch her hair care line - flawless. and you bet, this diva's life seems flawless alright - an enviable career, a successful hunk of a husband - dwayne wade, plus she's one hell of a looker!  gabrielle union is definitely living the life!! happy birthday girl!

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. it‚Äôs why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading ‚Äì which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs ‚Äì and he listened to wylie‚Äôs pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridge‚Äôs psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas it‚Äôs the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
happy birthday madam ellen johnson sirleaf! africa is blessed to have you. thank you for paving the way for many other women.
.
@regran_ed from @awloint -  we celebrate you our dear founder dr. elisha attai
.
regrann from @elishaattai -  not for us alone do we strive. we strive for the voiceless. we strive not for a place in history, but for a story in the hearts of our children; that they may have a place in the future where passion and vision forms an alliance, and cascades into generational change across boundaries.

it was truly an honor to be hosted by her excellency, ellen sirleef johnson, former president of liberia, nobel peace prize and mo ibrahim prize winner.... above all, an iconic african woman of worth. she colored my day beautifully with her endorsement of my book and some lovely comments.... "dr. attai, this is the best book i have seen celebrating and encouraging african women leaders. i'm really proud of you, i welcome you once again to liberia." i am grateful for this little contribution to celebrate and honor the african woman, and to raise, inspire our daughters to stand on their shoulders. this is definitely a must read book. 
we are now live on amazon. the tour is on!! let's go!!!!! african women of worth - 100 amazons volume 1 by dr. elisha attai.
