text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you‚Äôre waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn‚Äôt forthcoming. what most of them haven‚Äôt lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it. 
#nomore #adamcroasdell #eccarius #ignisscientia #lordbothwell #actor #voiceactor #ffxv #preacher #reign #vampire #supernatural #losangeles #women #supportwomen #timesup
instagram @adamcroasdell
twitter @acroasdell

text:
#dyk üîé globally, more than 1 in 3 women killed are killed by a male intimate partner. ‚õîÔ∏è nobody should be at risk from those who are supposed to love and care for them the most.
.
‚ÄºÔ∏è intimate partner violence is one of the most common forms of violence against women. it includes physical, sexual, and emotional abuse, and occurs across all socioeconomic, cultural and religious groups.  overwhelmingly, it is women who are the victims of such violence.
.
there are many reasons why women stay in violent relationships. preventing and responding to violence against women in the long-term is complex, and requires interventions across sectors and levels to tackle the deeply-rooted gender inequality which fuels it.
.
üßê learn more about what you can do by discovering lily's story on herstoryourstory.net (link in bio)

text:
things have happened here 
that i cannot quite find the words to convey. 
tragedies have lived and died here 
unforeseeable in the time of their stay. 
life has dragged and dulled 
against this body 
and i have still remained. 
and hope is here tomorrow,
unless i believe it today. -inside of this body

the notion that someone is perfect does not exist , i would rather not be or think i am perfect but what i do know is that i am not fake 
i have come across lots of fake people that i have walked away from and unfortunately have a few fake individuals that are surrounded by via the connection of my in-laws that are so fake in many ways and unfortunately think that they are perfect that actually they radiate so much negative energy because of the ego they carry. 
be the amazing person you can be , this is something we should all work towards. recognise that you are not perfect and don‚Äôt be that fake person.

text:
loyalty is often a way men enjoy intimacy with other men. while loyalty itself is of course a good thing, men systematically forge networks of fraternities, to the point where men completely unbeknownst to each other will still have a stake in a shared or imagined fraternity--a "#boysclub", one could call it. 
these networks and overall system of fraternity amongst men are founded upon hierarchy and exclusion, of men above women, men above gender fluid and nonconforming folx, men above children, men above, men above. this is a club based upon violence. 
this is a club that #harveyweinstein belongs to. this is a club that i inadvertently belong to, at least until i choose not to be a part of. men protect other men in this club, very much to the detriment and at the expense of others. 
this club upholds a strict policy of silence, denial, and defensiveness when challenged, when called on their bullshit. #metoo has been exemplifying this, but boundless other examples exist, such as the "blue wall"--the process by which police officers, still mostly male identified, working in a paternalistic and patriarchal occupation, protect each other at the expense of the rule of law.

this is a call to men. realise where these networks exist--both in the general patriarchal sphere of society, and specifically in your own networks. start to see how they work, and realise how violent, exclusionary, and bullshit they are. 
then, stop playing the game. hold the men in your life accountable. treat them like adults. recognize how by sheer privilege so much of what men do gets 'accepted' carte blanche. start to imagine a world where "loyalty" doesn't have to be the main form of intimacy between men, and where men don't stand for each other's violent and abhorrent behavior. 
start to dismantle or change these groups from the inside, because you have the privilege to do so.

text:
in october 2017, about a year ago, american actress alyssa milano posted a tweet that triggered what has since been known as the #metoo wave ‚Äì the standing up and speaking out pf those who have suffered sexual harassment or assault. milano wrote in her tweet, ‚Äúif you‚Äôve been sexually harassed or assaulted write ‚Äòme too‚Äô as a reply to this tweet.‚Äù this was a mere ten days after the new york times had published the harvey weinstein report, detailing how the hollywood producer had used his power and position for decades to sexually harass women and buy the silence of his accusers.
milano‚Äôs invitation spread like wildfire on social media and the #metoo floodgates opened with the hashtag #metoo being used over 12 million times within the first 24 hours on facebook alone. over the last couple of weeks, india has seen a return of the #metoo phenomenon, with women calling out sexual misconduct and harassment by scores of men from the worlds of film, television, journalism, business, art, writing, and stand-up comedy.
the hashtag has underlined the crucial role played by social media in enabling these women to come out with their stories.
the ongoing phase of the #metooindia campaign in india began in the last week of september, when former actor tanushree dutta alleged she had been harassed by actor nana patekar on a film set in 2008.

how does this movement affect the victims? we'll be talking about this for the next two weeks along with steps that you can take if you feel your mental health getting affected by it.

text:
i have been feeling an incredible desire from the depths of my soul, a need to be at the ocean and a feeling that the ocean needs me. do you ever feel that way? i have always been a forest and mountains gal. i see god in the mountains and the forests are a church to me. walking amongst the evergreen trees i feel as if they are reaching out their mighty branches and hugging me, hugging my soul, hugging all the dark in this world away so that it can't harm me. this makes me think of @elizabeth_gilbert_writer 's book big magic. have you read it? .
i love mother nature and i believe she loves us back. i also believe that she is hurting from deforestation as a result of the meat and dairy industry (amount other things). the over fishing of our oceans and the pollution within them. she is hurting but she is strong and resilient af. we need to do everything in our power to assist in her healing. what can we do to help her heal? what are you doing to help mother nature heal? i do it by being vegan and working towards my goal to get as close to zero waste as possible. there is no need for plastic in our lives anymore. there is no need. there is no need to eat meat anymore either. there is just no need. üì∏ by @sjanaelise 
p.s. this was jon and my first dance at our wedding. ‚ù§Ô∏è
name: Vegan Recipes by Rae Aflatooni

i love mother nature and i believe she loves us back. i also believe that she is hurting from deforestation as a result of the meat and dairy industry (amount other things). the over fishing of our oceans and the pollution within them. she is hurting but she is strong and resilient af. we need to do everything in our power to assist in her healing. what can we do to help her heal? what are you doing to help mother nature heal? i do it by being vegan and working towards my goal to get as close to zero waste as possible. there is no need for plastic in our lives anymore. there is no need. there is no need to eat meat anymore either. there is just no need. üì∏ by @sjanaelise 
p.s. this was jon and my first dance at our wedding. ‚ù§Ô∏è

text:
angry feminist, feminazi, feminichi are terms that have been hurled at me too often for me to start giving a fuck now. as i watch the #metoo movement rise, you know there‚Äôs some fury about the reactions i see. some men and some women have come out to claim that this movement is designed to create a divide between men and women and to them i say if you do not understand what this movement stands for shut up and learn. of all the people i‚Äôve met in my short existence very few have told me they have not been privy to abuse and might i tell you the people who have narrated stories of abuse include men. abuse is abuse, it can come at the hands of an unnamed stranger, a relative you know too well, a mutual friend you chose to trust or a boss with a reputation for being creepy. this movement is named me too and as is the case with feminism it fights for men and women, it talks about how power structures that are unequal breed abuse. this is our moment, so stand up and speak out and let go of the weight of toxic masculinity. i believe you and so do all the women who know abuse too well.

#feminist #feminichi #metoo #equality #toxicmasculinity #fuckthepatriarchy #silentspectator #letstalkaboutit #abuseisabuse

i was shocked still but ignored it all,

india will rise again,

unbottle the bottled feelings,
i am for me too

text:
resilience: the capacity to recover quickly from difficulties; toughness. üñ§
for me it isn‚Äôt about recovering quickly. for me that‚Äôs something that just isn‚Äôt possible. will i ever fully recover, probably not. as far as being tough? when i need to be. i find something extremely beautiful in being soft though. i toughened up and hardened myself to protect my heart, to be soft i found a vulnerability that forced me to face the demons in my head and to allow myself the opportunity to find peace and attempt to heal from my trauma. üñ§
i wear this bracelet to remind me that i am here, that i have survived the unimaginable, that i have a beautiful daughter who i was meant to have. she helped me find my strength while i helped her find her own. we are not who we were last year or the year before. we continue to grow and be better versions of ourselves. i am learning to take everything that broke me and to use the pieces to build a life that we deserve.
